Additional Equity Awards.
     (c) The Executive will be awarded additional equity grants under the Incentive Plan for each of the Company's 2011 and 2012 fiscal years as part of the regular annual grant process for the Company's executive officers (the ""). The New Equity Awards for each such fiscal year may be made before or after the start of the applicable 2010 or 2011 fiscal year, but will in all events be made at the same time as the other regular annual grants for that fiscal year. The total grant date fair value of the New Equity Awards for each such fiscal year will be at least $4 million and will be in a combination of stock options, restricted stock units and performance units/shares relating to shares of the Company's Class A common stock, as determined by the Compensation Committee in its sole discretion. The New Equity Awards for each of the Company's 2011 and 2012 fiscal years will have the same effective date and pricing date in effect for the other executive officer equity awards made for each such fiscal year.
New Equity Awards.
New Equity Awards
     (d) . The following terms and provisions will govern the various components of the New Equity Awards that are to be made to the Executive for the Company's 2011 and 2012 fiscal years pursuant to Section 4(c) above:
Vesting of New Equity Awards
 
          (i) The stock option component of each New Equity Award will vest in four (4) successive equal annual installments over the Executive's period of continued employment with the Company and will have a maximum term of six (6) years. Should the Executive's employment terminate for any reason other than (i) an involuntary termination for Cause (as such term is defined in Section 7(b) below), (ii) death or Disability (as such term is defined in Section 4(e) below) or (iii) a voluntary termination prior to August 31, 2012 other than for Good Reason (as such term is defined in Section 7(c) below), then each stock option will continue to vest in accordance with the foregoing vesting schedule, as if the Executive continued in employee status with the Company, and will remain exercisable, for any shares for which such option is at the time exercisable, until the earlier of (i) the expiration of the six (6)-year maximum term or (ii) the end of the twelve (12)-month period measured from the date on which the last annual installment of that stock option vests.
          (ii) The restricted stock unit component of each New Equity Award will have a performance-vesting condition tied to the fiscal year for such grant is awarded that will be the same as the performance-vesting condition applicable to the restricted stock unit awards made to the Company's other executive officers for that fiscal year. Upon the satisfaction of the applicable performance condition for the award, 25% of that award will vest on the last day of the fiscal year for which such award is made, with the shares of the Company's Class A common stock underlying that vested portion to be issued following the Compensation Committee's certification of the attained performance condition but not later than the close of the calendar year in which fiscal year ends, and the balance of the restricted stock units will vest, and the underlying shares issued, in three (3) successive equal annual installments, provided the Executive continues in the Company's employ through each such vesting date. However, should the Executive's employment terminate prior to the completion of the vesting schedule for any reason other than (i) an involuntary termination for Cause, (ii) death or Disability or (iii) a voluntary termination prior to August 31, 2012 other than for Good Reason, then the award will continue to vest (and the underlying shares issued) incrementally in accordance with the foregoing vesting schedule, as if the Executive continued in employee status with the Company.
          (iii) The performance unit/share component of each New Equity Award will have performance-vesting conditions measured over a performance period of one or more years that will be the same as for the other performance unit/share awards made to the Company's executive officers for the fiscal year for which that New Equity Award is made. Following the completion of the applicable performance period, the total number of shares of the Company's Class A common stock (if any) issuable under the award will be determined on the basis of the levels at which the applicable performance goals have in fact been attained. The number of shares so calculated will be issued to the Executive, following the Compensation Committee's certification of the level of performance goal attainment but not later than the close of the calendar year in which the performance period ends, provided (A) he continues in the Company's employ through the completion of the performance period or (B) there is an earlier termination of the Executive's employment for any reason other than (i) an involuntary termination for Cause, (ii) death or Disability or (iii) a voluntary termination prior to August 31, 2012 other than for Good Reason. In addition, should the Company's performance unit/share program in effect at the time such award is made to the Executive include any pro-rata vesting provisions, contingent upon performance goal attainment, for individuals who voluntarily leave the Company's employ prior to the completion of the performance period, then such provisions shall also be included in any performance unit/share award made to the Executive at that time.
          (iv) The continued vesting and exercisability of the stock options, the continued vesting of the restricted stock units and the vesting of the performance shares that is to occur, in accordance with the foregoing provisions of this Section 4(d), following the Executive's termination of employment with the Company shall in each instance be subject to his compliance with the confidentiality obligations under Section 9 of this Amended and Restated Agreement and the restrictive
 
covenants set forth in Section 10 of this Amended and Restated Agreement. Upon a material breach of such obligations or covenants by the Executive, all further vesting of his equity awards pursuant to the provisions of this Section 4(d) shall cease, and the unexercised stock options granted to the Executive as part of the New Equity Awards pursuant to Section 4(c) of this Amended and Restated Agreement shall immediately terminate.
     (e) Each component of the New Equity Awards made to the Executive pursuant to Section 4(c) of this Amended and Restated Agreement will also be subject to the partial vesting acceleration provisions of this Section 4(e) should his employment terminate by reason of death or Disability (as such term is defined below).
Partial Vesting Acceleration.
          (i) Should the Executive's employment with the Company terminate by reason of his death or Disability, the stock option component of each New Equity Award will immediately vest as to a portion of the unvested shares of the Company's Class A common stock subject to that option, and the option will remain exercisable for the vested shares for a twelve (12)-month period following his death or Disability, but not beyond the maximum six (6)-year term of the option. The number of shares that would vest on such an accelerated basis would be equal to the number of additional shares (if any) in which the Executive would have vested had he completed an additional eighteen (18) months of service following his death or Disability.
          (ii) No shares will be issued under any of the performance-based restricted stock unit or performance unit/share components of the New Equity Awards until the completion of the applicable performance period. At that time there will be determined the total number of shares (if any) issuable under the award based on the levels at which the applicable performance goals have in fact been attained and assuming the Executive had continued in the Company's employ through the completion of the applicable vesting schedule. Should any earlier termination of such employment occur by reason of the Executive's death or Disability, a portion of the total number of shares as calculated in accordance with the foregoing will vest on an accelerated basis, upon the later of (A) such termination of employment or (B) the completion of the applicable performance period. The accelerated portion will be equal to the number of additional shares (if any) in which the Executive would have vested had he completed an additional eighteen (18) months of service following the date of his death or Disability, and such accelerated portion shall be issued no later than the of (x) the fifteenth day of the third calendar month following the date of the Executive's death or Disability or (y) the end of the calendar year in which such death or Disability occurs; that in the event the Executive's Disability does not satisfy the definition of Permanent Disability below and the applicable award agreement is otherwise subject to Code Section 409A, the accelerated portion shall be issued on each applicable date on which the accelerated shares would have otherwise vested and become issuable, in accordance with the terms of the applicable award agreement, had Executive continued in employee status over that eighteen (18)-month period for which service credit is given hereunder.
later
provided, however,
          (iii) Should the Company have a more liberal vesting acceleration policy for death or Permanent Disability that is in effect at the time any equity award under Section 4(c) is made to the Executive, then that award will incorporate the terms and conditions of that more liberal policy.
          (iv) For purposes of this Section 4(e), shall mean the Executive's inability, by reason of any physical or mental injury or impairment, to perform, with or without reasonable accommodation, the principal duties and responsibilities of his position with the Company for a period of six (6) consecutive months or more; and shall mean the Executive's inability to engage in any substantial gainful activity by reason of any medically determinable physical or mental impairment that can be expected to result in his death or to last for a continuous period of twelve (12) months or more.
